<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>404 - Error Detected!</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/bootstrap.min.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
    <style>
        body, html {
            height: 100%;
            margin: 0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            font-family: 'Arial', sans-serif;
            background-color: #282c34;
            color: white;
        }
        .container {
            text-align: center;
        }
        .error-icon {
            font-size: 7rem;
            color: #ff6347;
        }
        .error-message {
            font-size: 2rem;
            font-weight: bold;
        }
        .hint {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            color: #bbb;
            margin-top: 20px;
        }
        .geeky-text {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: #888;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }
        .btn-home {
            margin-top: 40px;
            padding: 12px 24px;
            background-color: #008080;
            color: white;
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
        .btn-home:hover {
            background-color: #006666;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="error-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-bug"></i>
        </div>
        <h1 class="error-message">404 - Oops, This Page is Lost in the Code!</h1>
        <p>Looks like you’ve entered a page that doesn’t exist. Maybe it was swallowed by a black hole or deleted by a hacker with too much free time!</p>
        
        <div class="geeky-text">
            <p>Or maybe it was just a glitch in the Matrix. Either way, it’s gone (or it was never here).</p>
        </div>

        <div class="hint">
            <p>Don't worry, it's not your fault! Probably I (the developer) am working on something and screwed things up :(</p>
            <p>If you need to get back to safety, click the button below:</p>
            <p><a href="/" class="btn-home"><i class="fas fa-home"></i> Take me to the Home Page</a></p>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
